{meta: title Careless Hands}
{meta: artist Slim Whitman}
{meta: composer Bob Hillard and Carl Sigman}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]I let my heart fall [C]into careless [G]hands
[D7]Careless hands that broke my heart in [G]two
[C]You held my dreams like worthless grains of [G]sand
[D7]Careless hands don't care when dreams slip [G]through
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]I brought you joy and dear I loved you [G]so
[A7]But all that sunshine didn't make the roses [D7]grow
[G]If you don't change someday you'll know [C]the sorrow [Em]of
[G]Careless hands [D7]that can't hold on to [G]love
{end_of_verse}

